'''Dendrophilia''' (or less often '''arborphilia''' or '''dendrophily''') literally means "[[philia|love]] of [[trees]]". The term may sometimes refer to a [[paraphilia]] in which people are sexually attracted to or sexually aroused by trees. This may involve [[Human sexuality|sexual contact]] or veneration as [[phallic symbol]]s or both.<ref>{{cite book| title=The Dictionary of Psychology | page=263 | first= Raymond J. |last=Corsini | isbn=1-58391-028-X | publisher=Psychology Press | year=1999 }}</ref>

